d208c-10 | 2026-06-09T12:10:58Z | session:d208c058-7b2b-4ff8-bb82-d63623d51097 | `EventBuilder`, `Event`, `Filter` are all `nostr_sdk::prelude`. So a `Codec` impl can only ever be **another nostr wire-shape**. The seam swaps *NIPs*, not *transports*. The wiki's "intended swap-ins" — NMP (nostr), Marmot (MLS-*over*-nostr) — confirm the design quietly assumed the wire is always nostr events. "Support any transport" is true only inside the nostr family. \n  \n The most-coupled verb is `filters`. `Vec<Filter>` bakes in relay REQ semantics — a push/gossip transport doesn't subscribe by filter at all, it has a different fetch model entirely. That verb can't survive a real transport swap. [...] **1. Cut the seam along concerns, not kinds.** The `Codec` trait today fuses wire-mapping + subscription model + ACL (NIP-29 group management baked into `kind1`). The proposal replaces it with a **`FabricProvider`** that bundles four single-responsibility capabilities: \n  \n | Capability | Owns | \n |---|---| \n | **Lifecycle reactor** | side-effects of `ProjectOpened` etc. — nip29 creates a group, mls invites, kind1 no-ops | \n | **Membership source** | hydrates & streams the ACL from its native source | \n | **Wire codec** | pure `DomainEvent ⇄ envelope` | \n | **Delivery** | publish + subscribe-for-scope; owns REQ-filters / gossip / MLS-stream *privately* | \n  \n The `filters → Vec<Filter>` relay-REQ shape stops being on the public seam, so a push/MLS delivery model becomes expressible. [...] The fix is to push the boundary up to the types that are already abstract. Instead of codec-speaks-nostr + transport-plumbs-nostr (both nostr-typed), make the **transport** the seam and let it own the entire wire mapping internally: \n  \n ```rust \n trait Fabric { \n     async fn publish(&self, ev: &DomainEvent, as_agent: &Identity) -> Result<()>; \n     fn subscribe(&self, scope: &SubScope) -> impl Stream<Item = DomainEvent>; \n } \n ``` \n  \n Now `encode`/`decode`/`filters`/`EventBuilder` all become private implementation details of a `NostrFabric`. NIP-29 vs. open-relay becomes a *config of that fabric*, not a different `Codec`. And a non-nostr transport (MLS-native, gRPC) is a sibling `impl Fabric`, not an impossible-to-write `Codec`.
