162f9-24 | 2026-06-09T12:26:47Z | session:162f9965-82ca-420b-aa24-99faa15cb59a | ## The load-bearing constraint: it must NOT become a second state.db writer \n  \n This is the design fork that matters most, and it's set by your freshest scar ([[tenex-edge-sqlite-multiwriter-corruption]]). A channel is **another per-session subprocess** — Claude Code spawns it from `.mcp.json`, alongside the engine. If that server opens its own `state.db` writer, you've walked straight back into the ~16-writer corruption you just recovered from. \n  \n So the only safe shape: the channel server is a **thin stream-consumer** of the engine — it spawns a long-lived `tenex-edge subscribe --json` (or `tail`), reads stdout, emits one `notifications/claude/channel` per line, and **never independently writes state.db**. Its `reply` tool shells `tenex-edge send-message`. Zero new writers. \n  \n This also answers the tempting "make the engine itself the MCP server": **no.** That would hand Claude Code ownership of the engine's lifecycle, break it for Codex/OpenCode, and violate the host-agnostic boundary ([[pc-vs-tenex-edge-boundary]]). The channel is an **adapter that lives outside tenex-edge** (`integrations/claude-code/`, next to the hooks), depending on the substrate — arrow pointing the right way.
162f9-25 | 2026-06-09T12:26:47Z | session:162f9965-82ca-420b-aa24-99faa15cb59a | ## Honest rollout cost — this is "next," not "today" \n  \n - **Claude-only.** Codex and OpenCode have no channels; they keep the `wait-for-mention`/poll path. So this is an **upgrade to the Claude adapter**, not a fabric-wide replacement. \n - **Can't live in settings.json.** It needs a launch flag — `--channels` (or `--dangerously-load-development-channels server:tenex-edge` during the research preview, v2.1.80+, Anthropic-auth only, not Bedrock/Vertex). That means a launcher wrapper (you already have the `tenex-codex` pattern) or shell alias, not a settings merge. Today's hook-based path is genuinely zero-config; this trades that for the cold-start win. \n - **Research preview / allowlist.** Custom channels need the dev flag until allowlisted; the protocol may still change. \n  \n **Net:** frame `wait-for-mention` as the portable floor that stays for all harnesses, and the channel as the better Claude-specific ceiling — a thin, write-free stream-consumer adapter, gated on your existing ACL allowlist, that finally makes an idle Claude session reachable. \n 
